   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Annual Output Results</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. No. of customs officers sensitised / trained
2. No. of visits to the refrigerants dealers.
3. No. of cases of wrongly labelled, not adequate quality refrigerants identified.
4. Complete data submitted on time
5. Number of technicians trained
6. No of events organised on International Ozone Day(s).</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Domestic refrigeration sub-sector has recorded increase in the use of HCFC-based refrigerant blends, typically R406a as interim replacement for CFC-12 and R502 refrigerants resulting in the phase-in of increasing amounts of used refrigerators and freezers. The base year of HCFC consumption is set from 2009 representing 77.3 ODP tones.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2. At least one monitoring activity conducted nationwide.
4. Collect data on ODS consumption in Ghana for the year ending 2019.
6. At least 2 sensitisation sessions organised for public servants.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2. One monitoring activity was conducted in five (5) regions, where fifty-three (53) outlets (Importers, Distributors, and retailers of refrigerants) were visited.

4. Data collected for 2019.

6. 3 training workshops were organized for public servants in the (Kumasi Metropolitan Assembly, Suame Municipal Assembly and Efia Kwesimintim Municipal Assembly &#x2013; Takoradi on the Preservation of the Ozone Layer as part of annual international ozone day celebration. 137 public servants and Assembly members were engaged. Male -90; Female- 47</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2. Undertake at least one visit to a minimum of two regions to identify and isolate unapproved refrigerants on the market
4. Collect data on ODS consumption in Ghana for the year ending 2018.
5. Train at least 200 refrigeration technicians on use of acceptable refrigerants. 
6. Organize at least one event to celebrate the Ozone day.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2. Two monitoring visits were embarked to two (2) regions, four (4) towns and thirteen (13) outlets were visited. The number of personnel interacted with were thirty three (33) with thirty one (31) males and two (2) females. 

4. Data was collected country wide on Ghana&#x2019;s ODS consumption in the year 2018.

5. Training conducted for 400 technicians in five regions (western, Ashanti, Central, eastern and bono regions) 
on Hydrocarbon 290 refrigerant used in air conditioning systems.

6. Two events were organized for 807 second cycle students in the Bono and Upper West region where information was shared on Ozone layer protection under the theme: &#x201C;32 years and Healing&#x2019;&#x2019;.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
